				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${Y}\,=\,0.01476\,{X}\,-\,0.00134\,\left( {{R}^2\,=\,0.999} \right),$$\end{document}where, Y represents the absorbance of Gent at 333 nm and X represents the corresponding calculated Gent concentration (μg mL−1). The cumulative release was defined as mass of released Gent/mass of loaded Gent × 100%.

